### GraphQL API — /graphql (VS Code REST Client)
#
# 1. Run "login" first to capture a token.
# 2. The authorized queries reuse {{login.response.body.token}}.
# Tip: open http://localhost:8000/graphql/ in a browser for the Nitro IDE.

@host = http://localhost:8000
@contentType = application/json


### Login (REST) to obtain a token — run first
# @name login
POST {{host}}/auth/login
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "email": "alice@example.com",
  "password": "supersecret"
}


### me — WITH token (expect the current user)
POST {{host}}/graphql
Content-Type: {{contentType}}
Authorization: Bearer {{login.response.body.token}}

{
  "query": "{ me { id name email } }"
}


### me — WITHOUT token (expect AUTH_NOT_AUTHENTICATED)
POST {{host}}/graphql
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "query": "{ me { id name email } }"
}


### Introspection — list root query fields (no token needed)
POST {{host}}/graphql
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "query": "{ __schema { queryType { fields { name } } } }"
}
